<p align=center id=logop>
<a href="https://ProgressQuest.EnderAndrew.com" style="text-decoration:none"><img style="border:0" src="pq.gif" width="512px" height="451px" id="logo" title="Progress Quest Remix is the breakfast of not-quite champions who sleep in and let their game idle" alt="Progress Quest Remix" class="center"></a>
<div>
	<font color=#000032><br>
	<i>progressus imprimis</i>
		<h1 align=center> Realms are all on the original ProgressQuest.com server. I may eventually look into doing online play for Remix. </h1>
	<style>
	body { margin-left: 4em; margin-right: 4em }
	td { width: 20%; padding: 1ex; border: 1 solid #a0a0a0; background-color: #e0e0e0; color: black; vertical-align: top }
	</style><p><table border=0><tr><td><font size=+1><b>Knoram</b> </font><i>(pop. 73770)</i><br><a href=http://progressquest.com/knoram.php?>Hall of Fame</a> &middot; <a href=http://progressquest.com/knoram.php?cheaters=1>Hall of Infamy</a> &middot; <a href=/stats.php?realm=knor>Statistics</a><p>The oldest realm of Progress Quest, Knoram is home to more than fifty thousand characters, representing more than one million levels gained. That's a lot of dead wildlife. Knoram is the realm most favored by Demicanadian Bastard Lunatics.<p><td><font size=+1><b>Expodrine</b> </font><i>(pop. 101970)</i><br><a href=http://progressquest.com/expo.php?>Hall of Fame</a> &middot; <a href=http://progressquest.com/expo.php?cheaters=1>Hall of Infamy</a> &middot; <a href=/stats.php?realm=expo>Statistics</a><p>Follow the wooded path, turn left at the jellyrock, and proceed with caution. As you crest the last hummock and descry a goblin-dappled field of peonies, you've entered Expodrine. Sharpen your stick and polish your vambraces, and let's slay us some blink dogs.<p><td><font size=+1><b>Oobag</b> </font><i>(pop. 121650)</i><br><a href=http://progressquest.com/oobag.php?>Hall of Fame</a> &middot; <a href=http://progressquest.com/oobag.php?cheaters=1>Hall of Infamy</a> &middot; <a href=/stats.php?realm=ooba>Statistics</a> &middot; <a href=guilds.php>Guilds</a><p>Cower beneath a dark bespotted welkin, uneasy and alone, beset by chibits and keeks; gasp for a breathable lungfull among the belching pungaroles; and know, then, traveler - in your despair - that you are in the fell realm of Oobag! Bwaghh!<p><tr><td><font size=+1><b>Spoltog</b> </font><i>(pop. 53252)</i><br><a href=http://progressquest.com/spoltog.php?>Hall of Fame</a> &middot; <a href=http://progressquest.com/spoltog.php?cheaters=1>Hall of Infamy</a> &middot; <a href=/stats.php?realm=spog>Statistics</a> &middot; <a href=guilds.php>Guilds</a><p>Spoltog is a realm of dappled sunlight on golden fields where bugbears graze. In this magical land, silkies frolic on white sand beaches, and the buzz of grid bugs hints that killing is in the air.<p><td><font size=+1><b>Pemptus</b> </font><i>(pop. 191829)</i><br><a href=http://progressquest.com/pemptus.php?>Hall of Fame</a> &middot; <a href=http://progressquest.com/pemptus.php?cheaters=1>Hall of Infamy</a> &middot; <a href=/stats.php?realm=pemp>Statistics</a> &middot; <a href=guilds.php>Guilds</a><p>Home and eponym of the peripetaic fifth son of a mad king, Pemptus roils and shivers in tectonic agony. Pemptus the man and hero seethes too, never having known warm embrace save that of his magma motherland. Too, there is a guild so named, and a fiend, both mighty. And, some say,  yet another...<p><td><font size=+1><b>Alpaquil</b> </font><i>(pop. 5964)</i><br><a href=http://progressquest.com/alpaquil.php?>Hall of Fame</a> &middot; <a href=http://progressquest.com/alpaquil.php?cheaters=1>Hall of Infamy</a> &middot; <a href=/stats.php?realm=alpa>Statistics</a> &middot; <a href=guilds.php>Guilds</a><p>Rain, always rain. And hedgehogs. The hedgehogs are the result of an ambitious spell gone wrong, but the rain has ever fallen in Alpaquil. Oh there are sunny days, especially Neft of the mountains. But that's when the borlabs are at their worst!<p><tr><td colspan=3 align=center>
	<form action=/search.php style=display:inline>
		<input type=text name=name value='' size=30>
		<input type=submit value='Interrealm Search'>
		</form>
	</table>
	<p>
	<p style="padding: 1em; color: #404000; background-color: #ffffd0; border: solid 1 #a0a060">
	<i>
	<b>Of the Realms</b>
	<br>Plot Justification
	<br>
	<br>
	The time came that Voxor rebelled and ceased to heed Knoram, 
	Banthane of the Roilwachhs. Therefore, Knoram called once more 
	the great Roilwach Holmeet, held in his keep,
	Tob Lomen. At the Holmeet there was much discussion but little resolution, until at last,
	Spoltog lept upon the dias, and undraping his bolam and brandishing it aloft, cried
	that all must join in subduing Voxor, who must then be banished, until he should swear
	to again obey Knoram and the will of the Holmeet.
	<br>
	<br>
	But immediately there was a thunderous crash and a brilliant burst of light which
	shone keenly on every bandyclef, and from high on a buttress slid down Voxor, scowling
	in his wrath, though no word he spoke. And the guardians who saw looked in awe, for the dias had
	crumbled and the Roilward itself lay broken. 
	<br>
	<br>
	Then, Knoram arose and spoke, "So we must separate. Let each man make his choice and follow
	whom he will." And he departed, and in that hour the souls of the unborn chose, and the world
	layered upon itself, and the living dwelt with Knoram, but the unborn followed each 
	his own will, to whichever realm they had chosen.
	</i>
	</p>
	
	
